  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Cap assisted colonoscopy, a simple technique of fixing a transparent plastic cap to the tip
      of the colonoscope, was proven to increase the adenoma detection rate during screening
      colonoscopy by helping to depress and flatten colonic folds, thereby improving visualization
      and decreasing blind mucosal areas. The usefulness of cap assisted upper endoscopy (CAE) is
      still under investigations. The aim of this study is to compare the diagnostic yield of the
      CAE to the standard endoscopy in esophagus.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
